      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ اِشْتَرَى دَاراً بِرَقِيقٍ وَ مَتَاعٍ وَ بَزٍّ وَ جَوْهَرٍ فَقَالَ \"لَيْسَ لِأَحَدٍ فِيهَا شُفْعَةٌ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3379 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Ali ibn Ri'ab from Abu Abdullah (as): Regarding a man who bought a house using slaves, goods, fabric, and jewels.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no preemption (shufah) for anyone in this case.\""
        ]
      }
